1.title: Mini

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: It's all about a true British icon: the Mini. Brian visits the birthplace of the Mini, gets rally tips from a legend, and fulfills a lifelong dream.

2.title: Episode #1.2

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Bugatti is arguably the ultimate expression of sport, engineering, and artistic brilliance. Brian visit the Bugatti factory and smashes his own personal speed record.

3.title: Episode #1.3

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Rolls-Royce is a true British legend. Brian gets behind the wheel of one of the most celebrated motorcars in history. He then makes a special visit to the Rolls-Royce factory and uncovers the truth behind it's mascot.

4.title: Episode #1.4

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Brian dives head first into exploring the ravishing Italian icon: Lamborghini.

5.title: Porsche

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: It's one of the world's most legendary sports cars--Porsche. Brian visits the center of their empire in Stuttgart. He then whips the Porsche 917 around a track and scopes out Porsche's super-secret vault.

1.title: Jaguar

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Jaguar is a quintessentially British brand renowned for producing some of the world's most beautiful and successful sports cars. Brian will explore what makes the brand so special by taking a look at its illustrious heritage.

2.title: Land Rover

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: With the announcement that the Land Rover Defender production line is due to soon come to an end after 66 years, Brian will explore its rise to icon status.

3.title: Alfa Romeo

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Brian steps into the footsteps of one of his racing heroes by driving the P3, which Tazio Nuvolari drove in the 1930s.

4.title: McLaren

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Brian tours the McLaren Technology Centre, the iconic F1 brand's space-aged headquarters in Woking, UK, and has a go at being a pit mechanic. He also test drives the P1, the marque's current supercar, and a classic M6 Can-Am racer.

5.title: Nascar

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: NASCAR is one of America's biggest spectator sports with a history as colourful as the cars that battle it out each week on their oval circuits. Brian will delve into its origins and find a world of illegal moonshine running.

6.title: MG

episode of.title: Cars That Rock with Brian Johnson (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Brian visits the MG factory, which has produced sports cars that have enchanted the masses and created an impressive automotive heritage.

imdb.plot outline: When he's not wowing millions of screaming fans in one of the biggest and most influential rock bands of all time, AC/DC front man Brian Johnson can be found behind the wheel of a powerhouse car. He's competed in vintage races all over the globe and even participated in Daytona. Now Brian's going full speed ahead to his next adventure - sharing his passion for the most magnificent four-wheeled vehicles in history! From Porsche, Bugahtti and Lamborghini to Rolls Royce, Mini and Bentley, this bona-fide car fanatic takes us inside exclusive factories in Italy, Germany and England to uncover what makes them so iconic, talking with owners and experts to reveal the fascinating histories and mysteries of each ride and getting to the root of our need for speed with cars that inspire awe, envy and pride.
